title: Argentine peso plunges after Trump admirer nicknamed 'the wig' wins presidential primary
description: The Argentine peso has plunged in value after a man who admires Donald Trump won presidential primary elections.

title: Hawaii governor warns dozens more could be dead in wildfires
description: Hawaii's governor has warned that dozens more could be dead on the island of Maui following devastating wildfires - which have already claimed the lives of 96 people.

title: Trump set to face forgery charge from Georgia prosecutors - report
description: Georgia state prosecutors are set to bring charges including conspiracy to commit forgery against Donald Trump, Reuters reports.

title: 'Mud tsunami' smashes through Italian mountain town
description: A mudslide has been caught on camera as it dramatically ploughed through a street in an Italian town.

title: Escaped lion shot dead in South Korea
description: An escaped lioness has been shot dead in South Korea after an emergency search involving more than 100 police, firefighters and hunters.

title: RAF Typhoon jets intercept Russian bombers flying north of Scotland
description: RAF Typhoon jets intercepted Russian bombers flying north of Scotland in the early hours of Monday morning, the UK government has said.

title: Seeds from Hiroshima 'survivor tree' growing in Scotland as part of peace project
description: Seeds from a tree that survived the atomic bomb in Hiroshima are being grown in Glasgow.

title: Lionesses hope semi-final experience will help them reach World Cup final, Keira Walsh says
description: England are hoping their semi-final experience can give them an edge in their World Cup showdown against Australia on Wednesday, midfielder Keira Walsh has said.

title: Flight returns to Sydney after passenger 'threatens to blow plane up'
description: A passenger has been arrested after a flight from Australia to Malaysia was flown back to Sydney in what police called an "emergency incident".

title: Woman who cooked 'deadly' mushroom lunch says she ended up in hospital herself after meal
description: A woman who cooked a lunch that is believed to have left three people dead and one fighting for his life from a suspected mushroom poisoning has told police she also ended up in hospital after eating the meal.

title: Flights suspended as Mount Etna spews lava and ash
description: Sicily's Mount Etna has erupted, sending ash and lava high over the Mediterranean island, forcing flights to be suspended and leaving tourists facing holiday disruption.

title: Three women injured in 'vicious and relentless' otter attack
description: Three women were injured when an otter attacked them as they were floating down a river in an inflatable boat in Montana.

title: In pictures: How summer meteor shower peaked around the world
description: Stargazers were treated to the peak of the annual summer Perseid meteor shower over the weekend.

title: Kim wants power to 'surely annihilate' enemies as he orders sharp rise in missile production
description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un says he wants his army to have the power to "surely annihilate" its enemies as he called on suppliers to deliver more missiles ahead of planned US-South Korea military exercises.

title: At least 22 dead as monsoon rain triggers floods and landslides
description: At least 22 people have died and many others are trapped after monsoon rain triggered floods and landslides in India's Himalayan region.

title: 10th anniversary of the bloodiest day in Egypt's modern history
description: Ten years ago, Egypt was in turmoil as tens of thousands of Egyptians flooded the streets to demand change, ending in a notorious massacre.

title: Neymar set to become latest star footballer to join Saudi league
description: Brazil star Neymar is set to become the latest big-name footballer to join the Saudi league.

title: Mick Fleetwood loses restaurant in Hawaii wildfires - and says situation on the ground is 'catastrophic'
description: British rock star Mick Fleetwood, who has lived in Hawaii for decades, has said the situation in Lahaina is "catastrophic" following deadly wildfires that have killed at least 93 people.

title: Abandoned walrus pup given 'round-the-clock' cuddles has died
description: An abandoned walrus pup that was receiving round-the-clock "cuddling" from welfare workers has died.
